# Entity type organization

- All domain entity interfaces and types must be placed under `src/types/`.
- Organize by module, for example `src/types/production/mesLot.ts` for production-related entities.
- When creating or updating page code, import entity types from `src/types/...` instead of declaring new page-local entity types.
- Prefer one module folder per business domain to keep entity definitions reusable across pages, API layers, and stores.

# Examples

```ts
import type { MesLot } from '@/types/production/mesLot'
```

```ts
// Avoid declaring page-local entity types
script setup lang="ts"
type MesLot = {
  id?: string
}
```
